          "$x > 0$",
          "$x \ge 0$",
          "All real numbers",
          "$x \neq 0$"
        ],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "$(f/g)(x) = x^2 / \sqrt{x}$. Because $\sqrt{x}$ is in the denominator, $x$ must be greater than 0."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Evaluate $g(x+h)$ for $g(x) = 5x - 2$.",
        "options": [
          "$5x + 5h - 2$",
          "$5x + h - 2$",
          "$5x - 2 + h$",
          "$5xh - 2$"
        ],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "Replace $x$ with $(x+h)$: $g(x+h) = 5(x+h) - 2 = 5x + 5h - 2$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Given $f(x) = 3x$ and $g(x) = x^2$, find $(f \cdot g)(2)$.",
